                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@user3307073 I think it looks at first glance like &lt;code&gt;...result&lt;/code&gt; is the starting value, which is why it&apos;s so confusing (what is &lt;code&gt;...result&lt;/code&gt; if we haven&apos;t started building &lt;code&gt;result&lt;/code&gt; yet?). But starting value is is the second argument to &lt;code&gt;.reduce()&lt;/code&gt;, not the first, and that&apos;s down at the bottom: &lt;code&gt;{}&lt;/code&gt;. So you always start with a JS object. Instead, &lt;code&gt;...result&lt;/code&gt; is in the &lt;code&gt;{}&lt;/code&gt; that is passed to the first argument, so it means &quot;start with all the fields you already had (before adding the new one &lt;code&gt;item[key]&lt;/code&gt;)&quot;.&lt;/span&gt;

